    <p>That 117g gap isn't a nutrition debate — it's the difference between a travel week that costs you muscle and one that doesn't. Both days feel like "normal eating." Only one of them is working for you.</p>
    <h2>The Anchor Strategy — One Decision Per Meal</h2>

    <p>The most practical travel protein strategy isn't a meal plan — it's a single rule: <strong>protein is the first decision at every meal, not an afterthought.</strong> Before you look at anything else on the menu, identify the highest-protein option available. Build the meal around that. Everything else — sides, drinks, extras — fills in around the protein anchor.</p>

    <p>This one mental shift changes the entire math of a travel day. Instead of ordering what sounds good and hoping the protein works out, you lead with protein and treat the rest as optional.</p>

